<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-402-856  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 402 856.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  June 19 1989 v3 n25 p15(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Air Force center chief sees benefits in new computer division.andO;(Arlyn Schumaker)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brewin, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Colonel Arlyn Schumaker of the Air Force Standard Systems Center(SSC) is pleased with the creation of the Computer Systems Div(CSD), which will oversee the development, acquisition and supportof computer systems.andP;  The Air Force Computer Acquisition Centerand the SSC will be under the command of the CSD, which willperform some, though not all, of the work of the other offices.andO;Schumaker believes that the reorganization of the Air Force'scomputer acquisition offices will enable his own command, the SSC,to concentrate on its overburdened acquisition programs.andP;  The SSCfinalized 20 contracts worth $180 million in FY 1988, and thatfigure is expected to climb to $3 billion in FY 1989.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Air Force. Computer Systems Div.andO;ReorganizationMilitaryUnited States.Air Force.Standard Systems CenterGovernment Contracts.andO;Person:    Schumaker, Arlyn (attitudes).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>